AB  - Alluvial fans create a special type of flash flood threat, especially in
and and semi-arid areas where the fans support urban development. Most
of the cities in Iran have developed in such environments, and are
facing flash and urban floods because of the rapid growth of the cities,
and the deficiency of urban planning in the last four decades. The
present study aims at analyzing the urbanization effect on natural
drainage patterns and their immediate result, namely the increase of
vulnerability of the metropolitan city of Mashhad. Mashhad, as the
second religious metropolis of the world, and second metropolis of Iran
