AB  - Small hillside reservoirs are fundamental for the sustainability of the
water resources in the semi-arid region of Tunisia, where the government
has constructed small dams since 1990. However, flash floods and severe
erosion are jeopardizing the life of those small hydraulic structures
prompting an assessment of the vulnerability of semi-arid catchments to
erosion. In this study, we investigated the degree of erosion in 23
catchments by considering six variables related to erosion: the specific
sediment yield, the hypsometric integral, the topographic index, the
rainfall-related attribute as well as lithological and vegetation cover.
