spatial analysis models. The results of the spatial analysis model are
illustrated through the flood risk map, generated as a product of
temporal flood probability and vulnerability of the territory. These
results can be successfully used in territorial planning projects and in
the management of emergency situations, but can also be included in
other spatial analysis models of flood risk.
