AB  - This paper presents a study of the applicability of four satellite-based
rainfall algorithms using highly resolved data from the first Meteosat
Second-Generation satellite to derive hourly rain intensities. Saxony
serves as an example of the mid-latitude regions. The focus is on the
suitability of these algorithms to detect and to monitor (flash)
flood-related rain intensities. For this purpose, 9 days with high
rainfall amounts between May and August 2006 were analysed by comparing
the satellite rain intensities to gauge adjusted radar data. Five
different spatial resolutions were used to examine the effects of
spatial integration from small scale (18 km(2)) to large scale (57 600
