AB  - As part of the Copernicus Programme, Sentinel 1 (S1) synthetic aperture
radar (SAR) mission represents a unique monitoring tool whose
potentialities for hydrological risk mitigation need to be evaluated. To
this aim, S1-A derived soil moisture maps with high spatial resolution
(100 m) and moderate temporal resolution (12 days) were assimilated
within a time-continuous, spatially-distributed, physically based
hydrological model (Continuum) with the specific objective to evaluate
the impact on discharge predictions and (flash) flood modelling. A
