AB  - Indepth study of traditional resource management practices of the
indigenous people of Uttarakhand Himalaya reveals their appreciably
advanced understanding of the causes of various hazards. Through their
continued keen observation, experimentation, innovation and
recordkeeping these people devised techniques of maximizing resource
availability while minimizing the wrath of the hazards. For ensuring
universal compliance of the rules so laid down these people relied on
social sanctions and religio -magical practices interwoven around little
tradition of the people. With weakening social solidarity in the recent
times these practices are last loosing ground and if adequate steps are
not taken for documention this rich knowledge of generations could well
be lost forever. These practices are highly relevent even today and hold
the key to minimizing losses due to natural hazards in a cost effective
and sustainable manner and are therefore required to be studied,
