AB  - Land use planners and drainage engineers require, among other
information, a clear map that delineates land subject to flash flooding
before they can approve residential development. Through the application
of spatially distributed models, the topographic wetness index (TWI) can
be determined as an alternative to the traditional approach of
delineating flood-prone areas using contours alone. The TWI provides a
