AB  - A multidisciplinary methodology for historical floods reconstruction was
applied to 1874 Santa Tecla floods occurred in Catalonia (NE Iberian
Peninsula), using both historical information and meteorological data
from 20th Century Reanalysis.
The results confirmed the exceptionality of the event: the highest
modeled specific peak flow was around 14.6 m(3) s(-1) km(-2) in a 100
km(2) catchment and all the modeled total rainfall values were above 110
mm in about six hours, with maximum intensities around 60 mm min(-1).
