AB  - Nuweiba sits on a flood plain between the Sinai Mountain and the Gulf of
Aqaba. Flash floods pose significant threats to socio-economic
development in the region. This study assessed flash floods risk in the
greater Nuweiba area in support of mitigation planning. Our approach
evaluated topographic, hydrological, and geological factors holistically
to rank areas of high, median, and low flash floods risk along the Wadi
Watir. Data from field surveys, Enhanced Thematic Mapper (ETM+) imagery,
and Shuttle Radar Terrain Model (SRTM) were analyzed through digital
