AB  - This paper focuses on the influence of mountain rain-on-snow (ROS)
events that can on occasion trigger major floods in alpine catchments.
In order to assess the evolution of these events in a recent past, and
the potential changes that could be experienced in a changing climate
over coming decades, we have focused on a small catchment in
north-eastem Switzerland, the Sitter, well-endowed with both climate and
hydrological data. Observations show that there has been an increase in
the nuinber of rain-on-snow events since the early 1960s related to the
