AB  - Vehicle-related deaths comprise more than half of all flash flood
fatalities in the United States. Using the publication Storm Data from
the United States National Climatic Data Center, we found 555
vehicle-related flood deaths that occurred in 355 flooding events during
19952005. Males accounted for 60% of the deaths. The difference in
