AB  - The influence of land use changes on flood occurrence and severity in
the Bisagno River (Thyrrenian Liguria, N.W. Italy is investigated using
a Monte Carlo simulation approach (Rulli and Rosso, 2002). High
resolution land-use maps for the area were reconstructed and scenario
simulations were made for a pre-industrial (1878), an intermediate
(1930) and a current (1980) year. Land-use effects were explored to
assess the consequences of distributed changes in land use due to
agricultural practice and urbanisation. Hydraulic conveyance effects
were considered, to assess the consequences of channel modifications
associated with engineering works in the lower Bisagno River network.
