AB  - Perceptions of flash floods and landslides were analyzed in four
communities of the Bavarian Alps using the mental model approach.
Thirty-eight qualitative interviews, two telephone surveys with 600
respondents, and two onsite interviews (74/95 respondents) were
conducted. Mental models concerning flash floods are much better
developed than those for landslides because the key physical processes
