AB  - There is observational evidence that hydrometeorological extremes, such
as heavy rainfall events, have become more frequent and intense in the
last decades around the world. In Brazil, intense rainfall events that
triggered flash floods and landslides were responsible for 74% of the
deaths related to natural disasters in the 1991-2010 period. To evaluate
Brazil's hot spots of vulnerability to these disasters, two indices were
