AB  - Floods modify the natural dynamics of river environments and greatly
affect urban areas, especially in mountain regions where flooding is
frequent because of the precipitation characteristics and orographic
configuration. In this study the vulnerability of the central sector of
the Pyrenees to flood events was investigated using frequency analysis
of daily flow and precipitation data for the period from 1940 to 2012
for the headwaters of the Aragon and sera rive. The land use evolution
