AB  - In most cases, flash floods and off-plain flooding occur locally,
sometimes far away from a watercourse. They happen in great number every
year, taking everyone completely by surprise. The losses from single
events are in the order of four- to six-digit euros, but may reach more
than one hundred million in some cases, even locally. Land-use changes,
increasing values and vulnerabilities, and climatic changes have lead to
more frequent and costly incidents of this kind. Structural protection
against this type of hazard is very limited, because any given place can
be hit. Early warning and reaction to an alert do not guarantee much
protection either, as these events happen too rapidly. The best way to
manage the risk of flash floods is to seek natural perils insurance. The
prerequisite for sufficient market penetration is to increase the
understanding and awareness of people that everyone is exposed to such a
surprise event.
