AB  - This study describes the investigation conducted for flood risk
assessment in urban areas using SIR-C data. The Athens basin is a
densely populated area with approximately four million inhabitants,
affected very often by destructive flash-floods. These flood phenomena
occur mainly at the margins of the urban area very close to the
surrounding mountains. The SIR-C image, acquired on October 2nd, 1994,
has been processed for speckle reduction and additionally a non-linear
stretching has been applied. After the first observations at every
single image, a false colour composite image was created using L-band
HV, C-band HH, and L-band HH as R,G,B. The captured information concerns
morphology (topography, slopes, gullies), land use and land cover,
drainage characteristics and building shell extension, density and block
orientation.
