Wadi Mousa and to determine the magnitude of flows for flash flood
hazards and construct Floodplain Zone maps for the selected flood return
periods of 25, 50, 75 and 100 years. Wadi Mousa is considered an
ephemeral wadi with intermittent flash flood of flows that can exceed
the 298 m(3)/s threshold. Its floods, however, do not flow every year.
Nevertheless, at certain years the extent of flood can be huge. The
surface drainage may be broadly divided into sub-catchments according to
drainage namely; Wadi Als-Sader, Wadi Jelwakh with Wadi Khaleel, Wadi
