infrequent flash floods generated by heavy rainstorm over the catchment
and flows to Wadi Araba. Average annual rainfall of Wadi Mousa was
calculated of 178 mm, and average annual evapotranspiration is 1300 mm
per year. The runoff analysis indicates that only rainfall events
exceeding 22 mm within the 24 hour period would generate runoff. (C)
