AB  - As flash flood events are becoming more frequent, the development of
flood risk estimation methods is becoming more important than ever
before. The aim of this paper is to develop a methodology in order to
study the flood risk in a river catchment by taking into account various
parameters that are organized in a spatial database (geological,
geomorphological, topographic and land use data). The collected data are
analyzed through the use of G.I.S software (ArcMap) in order to generate
the appropriate steps for the formation of the flood risk model.
