on the logistic regression) using as variables the lithology, the slope,
land use, average basin altitude. All the above variables are multiplied
by the proper weightsin the form of triangular fuzzy numbers. These
weights are related to the importance of each involved variable. This
model has been applied in the area of Samos Island, Greece with success.
The proposed methodology and the preliminary results, as exported for
the entire island prove the suitability of this method in the creation
of flood risk maps.
