AB  - To anticipate floods, the French current crisis management system uses
two tools. On one hand a meteorological vigilance provided by
Meteo-France, and on the other hand a flood vigilance coming from the
flood forecasting services.
After several flash floods of the lasts years, a feedback has shown how
difficult it is for some operators in the field to appropriate
information from these forecasts. There is some confusion between
vigilances and warnings, and between the different geographical levels
such as the whole department for Meteo-France vigilance, or monitored
