AB  - In July 2008, five people were killed by a tragic flash flood caused by
a local torrential heavy rainfall in a short time in Toga River.
Fromthis tragic accident, we realized that a system which can detect
hazardous rain-cells in the earlier stage is strongly needed and would
provide an additional 5 to 10 min for evacuation. By analyzing this
event, we verified that a first radar echo aloft, by volume scan
observation, is a practical and important sign for early warning of
flash flood, and we named a first echo as a ``baby-rain-cell{''} of
Guerrilla-heavy rainfall. Also, we found a vertical vorticity criterion
for identifying hazardous rain-cells and developed a heavy rainfall
prediction system that has the important feature of not missing any
