AB  - Information given on flash floods in real time should undoubtedly
correspond to the citizens needs as well as to the politics and the
safety guidelines. To supply this objective, Numerical Social Networks
(NSN) and smartphone applications could positively complete the official
institutional system, especially by means of the dynamic nature of
shared contents, and with the social interactions they support.
Nonetheless, even if several countries (United States or Philippines for
example) already use these systems to warn the population in case of
future floods, and even if the French government launched a specific app
the 2016 June 8th (namely SAIP), the French citizens and stakeholders do
not always use them during the alert process. This is generally
explained by the French protection system on individual data, the lack
