AB  - The coast is one of the areas most affected by natural hazards, with
floods being the most frequent and significant of these in terms of
their induced impacts, so any management scheme requires their
evaluation. In coastal areas, flooding is a hazard associated with
different processes acting at different scales: coastal storms, flash
floods and sea level rise (SLR). To address the problem as a whole, this
study presents a methodology to undertake a preliminary integrated risk
assessment of the magnitude of each flood component, taking into account
their scope (extension of the affected area) and their temporal scale.
