AB  - Flood hazard maps are one of the main components of any flood risk
management strategy. It is predicted that the degree of flood risk is
going to significantly increase in the future due to climatic and
environmental changes, and hence it is increasingly important that
state-of-the-art methods are implemented for assessing human stability
in floodwaters. Therefore, this paper focuses on proposing more accurate
and detailed guidelines for predicting flood hazard indices in small and
steep river basins or catchments, prone to the occurrence of flash
