(Lleida, Spanish Pyrenees), displays active erosional and depositional
phenomena caused by periodic torrential floods. These events present a
potential risk and incur significant economic losses. In ungauged remote
catchments (like Portaine), trees might be the only paleohydrological
source of information regarding past floods. Thus, we estimated the
temporal and spatial distribution of torrential floods by
dendrogeomorphological techniques to assess whether human impact
(land-use changes and infrastructure works) affected their frequency
