AB  - Flash floods cause damages and need emergency actions especially in
urban areas. Flood forecasting and flood warning systems (FFFWSs) can be
used for reducing flood damages and saving lives in areas vulnerable to
flooding. However, researches are needed to evaluate the effect of
urbanisation and the significance of implementing catchment-management
plan (ICMP) on FFFWS. This paper describes a framework proposed to
assess the impact of ICMP on expected lead time (ELT) of flash-flood
warning and it was applied for an urbanised steep catchment in an arid
