AB  - The frequent extreme weather events have led to dramatic urban
waterlogging and flash flood hazards in recent years, which result in
heavy casualties and serious economic losses. Mountainous cities like
Fuzhou, China, usually experience both types of hazard concurrently and
are susceptible to these hazards. Therefore, it is necessary to take
comprehensive defense measures to prevent and/or mitigate the impacts of
these hazards. In this study, the authors first reviewed the progress of
prevention measures of these two types of hazards in China through the
nationwide construction of sponge cities and national flash flood
prevention projects. The authors then analyzed the characteristics of
